The backbone of Ridgewood's defenses. Only a handful of recruits have ever made it to the Knight of Law rank, and they are something to be feared - for good reason. They are equipped with the mightiest of swords, the strongest of shields, and move with power unmatched by most mortal men.
A charming man in his early forties, the King of Cetha is popular and beloved of his people. He has dark hair and brilliant blue eyes that glimmer with intellect.

It’s a well known fact that elves are foppish gits, barely able to lift their own swords without a limp-wristed floppy motion. It was for this very reason that these boots were forged. 

The master elven smith Yal’driirmathileh Mastiiramaeviil, spent many long hours making these boots for the elven protectors of the long forgotten court of Myth Drannor. When the kingdom fell, many of these boots were lost, some fell into the hands of those responsible for the fall, others are a prized possession from a dragons hoard. 

Perhaps the adventurer who has stumbled upon them now will use them to serve their intended purpose. Perhaps though, they have simply made another step along the road to obscurity.

The Secret Sash is actually a more noteworthy item due to it's secret stash  of various elicit substances.  Unkown to most, but enjoyed by a curious few, these rare leaves and powders are hidden within various small slits along the belt.  When ingested, the powerful herbs have a way of instilling a confident bliss in the user, aiding performers and entertainers with a euphoric ease.  Typically, Harpers have controlled the flow of these most enjoyable belts.
Created in great quantities by long forgotten mages, these weapons were apparently designed for sell or outfitting of armies.
